<p>In most of the stdlib code example for FILE is see something like this:</p>  <pre><code> FILE * pFile;  pFile = fopen ("myfile.txt" , "r");  if (pFile == NULL) ... </code></pre>  <p>or</p>  <pre><code> FILE * pFile = NULL;  pFile = fopen ("myfile.txt" , "r"); </code></pre>  <p>What is the reason do not use</p>  <pre><code> FILE * pFile = fopen ("myfile.txt" , "r"); </code></pre>  <p>or</p>  <pre><code> FILE * pFile = NULL;  if (NULL == (pFile = fopen ("myfile.txt" , "r"))) ... </code></pre>  <p>?</p>